WITH grp AS (
    select 
      t1.BARCODE as ean1, t2.BARCODE as ean2, count(distinct t1.RECEIPTID) as orders,
      rn = ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY t1.BARCODE order by count(distinct t1.RECEIPTID) desc)
    from 
    (
        select
           RECEIPTID, BARCODE
        from RBOTRANSACTIONSALESTRANS
        where convert(date, TRANSDATE) >= CAST(DATEADD(day, -30, GETDATE()) as DATE)
    ) as t1
    inner join (
        select 
           RECEIPTID, BARCODE
        from RBOTRANSACTIONSALESTRANS
        where convert(date, TRANSDATE) >= CAST(DATEADD(day, -30, GETDATE()) as DATE)
    ) as t2 
    ON t1.RECEIPTID = t2.RECEIPTID AND t1.BARCODE != t2.BARCODE
    WHERE t2.BARCODE != '' and t1.BARCODE != '' and t1.BARCODE != '05' and t2.BARCODE != '05' and t1.BARCODE != '06' and t2.BARCODE != '06' and t1.RECEIPTID != ''
    group by t1.BARCODE, t2.BARCODE
)
SELECT ean1, ean2, orders from grp 
where rn <= 4
order by ean1, ean2, orders desc
